2054.subject: HPWE
2054.descrlong: A hands-on class that incorporates the four components of self-defense: awareness, avoidance, and verbal and physical techniques. Teaches verbal and physical self-defense skills from a standing position and from the ground. This class is essentially a rape-prevention course that aims to reduce fear and empower students with skills to defend themselves against sexual attacks. (Offered every semester.)
